# Reset Worker Node (If Join Failed)

```bash
sudo kubeadm reset -f
```

```bash
sudo rm -rf /etc/kubernetes/pki
```

```bash
sudo rm -rf /var/lib/kubelet/*
```

```bash
sudo rm -rf /etc/cni/net.d
```

Restart:

```bash
sudo systemctl restart containerd
```

```bash
sudo systemctl restart kubelet
```

---

# Join Worker Node to Cluster

Run the join command generated from master node:

```bash
kubeadm join <MASTER-IP>:6443 --token <TOKEN> \
--discovery-token-ca-cert-hash sha256:<HASH>
```

Example:

```bash
kubeadm join 172.31.26.147:6443 --token tij06v.kb2vqjikgd2ruml8 --discovery-token-ca-cert-hash sha256:9f1422c5f3a2817b6ea9a4383d940c2993412f8f1565fba22d0863373dacd2d8
```

---

# Verify Worker Node from Master

Run on master node:

```bash
kubectl get nodes
```

Expected Output:

```text
NAME               STATUS   ROLES           AGE   VERSION
ip-172-31-26-147   Ready    control-plane   XXm   v1.29.15
ip-172-31-22-63    Ready    <none>          XXm   v1.29.15
```

